title: monic cubics (coef<=20)
shortdesc: Roots of monic integral cubics with negative discriminant
longdesc: Roots of monic integral cubics with negative discriminant.  The point in H^2 is the root in the upper half plane.  The point in the boundary of H^2 is the real root. (Added on the suggestion of the Algebraic Starscapes team: Pierre Arnoux, Edmund Harriss, Katherine Stange, and Steven Trettel)
